<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">THE ENCHANTER'S MESMERIZATION SPELL:  A GROUP SAVER</b></font> - <small>Sanveen Xin`Huai <Legacy>, Tarew Marr</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    Has your group ever been overcome by to many mobs?<P>Mesmerization will save you and your group's life with a properly informed/educated group, in the right area.<P>
<P>
Here are some tips on how to use it:<P>
<P>
1. Inform your group that you have Mesmerization memorized and that it is a AoE stun/hate wiping spell.<P>
<P>
2. Tell them it will stun you if to close to the targeted mob!<P>
<P>
3. Tell everyone in the group to always /assist the main tank of the group. This is very important, even when not using this spell.<P>
<P>
4. When the people in your group notice "suchandsuch has been Mesmerized" Have them all back away, out of agro range of the mobs emediately, even if a few mobs didn't get mez'd.  I have a hot-key that says "Back away! Out of agro range!" made for this purpose.<P>
<P>
5. Inform other casters in the group not to use AoE damage/debuff spells! They'll just re-agro all your nicely mez'd monsters.<P>
<P>
6. If your group panics and runs the mob into you, use Color flux/shift to stun them, then back out to safety, then cast mez.<P>
<P>
7.  When using this spell indoors or in dungeons, use extreme care not to stun yourself.  Use the Color series instead if in close quarters.<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
It may take awhile for your group to understand the concept, but with patience, they will be trained proper, and future enchanters will love you for it!<P>
<P>
Using this tactic has saved the lives of everyone in my groups many times and increased the incoming XP drastically.<P>
<P>
Don't panic if everything doesn't get mez'd, that's why eveyone backs out of agro range of the mez'd mobs and only attacks the Tanks target, simply recast again, unless of course there are deep reds in the mob.<P>
<P>
I've had to do this 3 times in a row to clear a mob of 15+ monsters.  When done right, everyone lives through it, and can continue fighting without delay.<P>
<P>
The color series of spells can work simuliar to this, but I find the agro factor to be to risky.<P>
<P>
After some awed people have seen this on the sidelines, they usually will always want an enchanter in their group from then on. :)<P>
<P>
<P>
Safe Hunting!

    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
